                    <span>This was a great second to the Lost Years of Merlin books. In this story Stagmar has been defeated and the Treasures of Fincarya are found and saved from the destruction of the Shrouded Castle. However things are not well yet. The warrior goblins and wights still walk the land, though not as profucely as before. The blight still covers much of Fincarya. A council is called. There it is decided that the Flowering Harp, one of the Treasures of Fincarya, is to be place in the hands of Merlin, a young wizard who took his name in memory of Trouble (a troublesome merlyn in the first book). Merlin's stask is to heal the land from the blight and not to be swayed by anything until his quest is done. Eventually Merlin finds himself on the shore where he first landed on Fincarya. Merlin has missed his mother, Elen of the Saphirre Eyes, and,using his powers and the help of the wise sea shell, brings her to Fincarya. However Rhit Gwar lays a trap for Merlin, hoping to kill him. The deadly trap is instead tripped by Elen, the only cure being made by Dadga in the Otherworld. Merlin must now master the souls of the seven songs of wizardry, written in Abrassa by Tathana, Merlin's Grandfather. Once he masters the songs he must also defeat a giant with a look that literally kills.
<br /></span>
                  
