                    </div>
                    <span>The Seven Songs of Merlin by T.A. Barron
<br />
<br />   The Seven Songs is a great book by one of my favorite authors. Merlin is a young 14 year old kid. He doesn't thing he has what it takes to be a wizard. Being the Grandson of Tuatha the greatest wizard of his time. He feels in the shadow of something greater.
<br />   The Plot has a lot to do with the title. Merlin abandons his quest in the dark hills and goes to see his mother Elen. To bring her to Fincayra he must find the wisest of the speaking shells. Then an unexpected twist comes. His mother becomes hanging for life at the edge of one month. Now with the fate of his own mother in his hands he must find the souls of the seven songs passed down by Tuatha. Now the clock is ticking and he must now defeat a terrible ogre to enter the otherworld to save his mother.
<br />   This book takes place all over the magical island of Fincayra. This book has seven morals one for each song. Like "every creature has the ability to change." and "the strongest bonds are in the heart." and others.
<br />   I loved this book because it taught me 7 things. Also because I love this specific genre. The Seven Songs of Merlin is a great book that everyone can get excited about!
<br />
<br />-Kevin P. L.</span>
                  
